    "This variance in the early years may be linked to the nascent stage of GeoGebra, which was officially launched in 2006 (Chrysanthou, 2008; Diković, 2009; Hohenwarter & Jones, 2007; Hohenwarter & Lavicza, 2007; Hohenwarter & Preiner, 2007; Mehdiyev, 2009; Preiner, 2008), and its incremental recognition within the international mathematics education sphere.",
    "The period between 2010 and 2013 witnessed a noticeable escalation in article production.",
    "However, a decline was registered in 2014, with a decrease of nine articles from the preceding year.",
